cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method to learn the parameters of a deep model in one shot, which is related to machine learning and deep learning. The experiments involve learning characters from single exemplars in Omniglot and tracking visual objects from a single initial exemplar in the Visual Object Tracking benchmark, which are related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the experiments involve natural language processing, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
